The paper deals with resource allocation in cooperative wireless networks, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The use of linear programming in the algorithm suggests that it may also fall under the category of optimization (cs.DC). The exploitation of spatial and temporal diversity in the network suggests that it may also fall under the category of signal processing (cs.SI) and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
